entries.content: The complete title copyrighted for the second song is "It Don’t Mean a Thing (If It Ain’t Got that Swing)". "Lazy Rhapsody" was issued with the title "Swanee Rhapsody" on most copies of Br 6288. The song was never copyrighted under either title; "Lazy Rhapsody" is the title used on most reissues.

entries.content: The DE3202a-b-c stereo medley is reproduced in true stereo on the EV-3005 LP and on the RCA and Natasha Imports CDs. The stereo medley consists of a left channel, sourced from one disc (LBRC-71811-1), and synchronized with a right channel from another (LBSHQ-71812-2). RCA (F) 741.085, which claims to issue the latter, was transferred from a test pressing of the former.

entries.content: This first-ever recording of Sophisticated Lady was recorded under the title of My Sophisticated Daddy. We know this to be the same song because the co-composers are noted in Victor's files as "Duke Ellington-L. Brown-Otto Hardwick.". Takes -1 and -2 were made by RCA of all titles recorded at this session, included Maori; none of them survived, except a test of Maori take -1.
